abstract: |
  A comprehensive unified framework combining fundamental physics derivations
  with open-source computational therapeutic pipelines.

  PHYSICS (Z = 2√(8π/3) = 5.79):
  - MOND acceleration scale: a₀ = cH₀/Z
  - Dark energy fraction: Ω_Λ = 3Z/(8+3Z) = 0.685 (0.04% accuracy)
  - Fine structure constant: α = 1/(4Z²+3) = 1/137.04 (0.003% accuracy)
  - 62+ observables with average accuracy 0.7%

  THERAPEUTICS (v5.0 - Prior Art Established April 20, 2026):
  - Dark Proteome: c-Myc binders via REMD for cancer (70% of human cancers)
  - Ion Channels: NaV1.7 knottin blockers for non-addictive pain (opioid alternative)
  - Metalloenzymes: Thermostable PETase (+20°C) for plastic bioremediation
  - CFTR Chaperones: Peptide stabilizers for cystic fibrosis
  - D2R Agonists: Selective peptides for prolactinoma
  - Antimicrobial Peptides: De novo AMPs for antibiotic resistance

  Includes 3-layer cross-validation (ESMFold/AlphaFold consensus, stereochemical QA,
  thermal stress MD) to detect ML hallucinations. All therapeutic sequences published
  as prior art under AGPL-3.0 + OpenMTA to prevent patent enclosure.

